  "texts": [
    "For solenoidal fields (e.g.",
    "a primordial magnetic field or vortical bulk fluid motion) characterised by a typical correlation scale of the order of the turbulence scale λ *, it is constant for f < 1/λ *.",
    "Furthermore, it decays as f -11/3 for f 1/λ *, if the turbulence is of the Kolmogorov type, as we assume here.",
    "Hence, the resulting spectral shape of the GWB in Eq.",
    "(21) presents three power laws: f 3 at frequencies below the inverse effective duration of the turbulence f < 1/δt fin, f at intermediate frequencies 1/δt fin < f < 1/λ *, and f -8/3 at large frequencies f > 1/λ *."
  ],
